From: Pauli Virtanen <pav@iki.fi>
Date: Sun, 21 May 2023 15:48:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Bluetooth: ISO: consider right CIS when removing CIG at cleanup
Git-commit: 31c5f9164949347c9cb34f041a7e04fdc08b1b85
Patch-mainline: v6.4-rc6
References: git-fixes

[ backport note: drop ucast field as we didn't backport 0fe8c8d07134 yet ]

When looking for CIS blocking CIG removal, consider only the CIS with
the right CIG ID. Don't try to remove CIG with unset CIG ID.

Fixes: 26afbd826ee3 ("Bluetooth: Add initial implementation of CIS connections")
Signed-off-by: Pauli Virtanen <pav@iki.fi>
Signed-off-by: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.von.dentz@intel.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 net/bluetooth/hci_conn.c |    7 +++++--
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/bluetooth/hci_conn.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/hci_conn.c
@@ -876,8 +876,8 @@ static void find_cis(struct hci_conn *co
 {
 	struct iso_list_data *d = data;
 
-	/* Ignore broadcast */
-	if (!bacmp(&conn->dst, BDADDR_ANY))
+	/* Ignore broadcast or if CIG don't match */
+	if (!bacmp(&conn->dst, BDADDR_ANY) || d->cig != conn->iso_qos.cig)
 		return;
 
 	d->count++;
@@ -892,6 +892,9 @@ static void cis_cleanup(struct hci_conn
 	struct hci_dev *hdev = conn->hdev;
 	struct iso_list_data d;
 
+	if (conn->iso_qos.cig == BT_ISO_QOS_CIG_UNSET)
+		return;
+
 	memset(&d, 0, sizeof(d));
 	d.cig = conn->iso_qos.cig;
 
